{"title_page": "Orhan Akta\u015f", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Orhan Akta\u015f\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1994|10|21|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[W\u00fcrselen]], [[Germany]]\n| height         = {{height|m=1.75}}\n| position       = [[Defender (association football)|Left back]]<ref>{{WorldFootball.net|orhan-aktas}}</ref>\n| currentclub    = [[Manisa FK]]\n| clubnumber     = \n| youthyears1    = \n| youthclubs1    = Blau-Wei\u00df Alsdorf\n| youthyears2    = {{0|0000}}\u20132010\n| youthclubs2    = Germania D\u00fcrwi\u00df\n| youthyears3    = 2010\u20132013\n| youthclubs3    = [[Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach|Borussia M'gladbach]]\n| youthyears4    = 2013\u20132014\n| youthclubs4    = [[Denizlispor]]\n| years1         = 2014\u20132015\n| clubs1         = [[Husqvarna FF]]\n| caps1          = 20\n| goals1         = 0\n| years2         = 2015     \n| clubs2         = [[PFC Haskovo|Haskovo]]\n| caps2          = 10\n| goals2         = 0\n| years3         = 2015\u20132018\n| clubs3         = [[\u0130stanbulspor A.\u015e.|\u0130stanbulspor]]\n| caps3          = 65\n| goals3         = 1\n| years4         = 2018\u20132019\n| clubs4         = BB Bodrumspor\n| caps4          = 42\n| goals4         = 2\n| years5         = 2019\n| clubs5         = [[Giresunspor]]\n| caps5          = 0\n| goals5         = 0\n| years6         = 2020\u2013\n| clubs6         = [[Manisa FK]]\n| caps6          = 0\n| goals6         = 0\n| nationalyears1 =           \n| nationalteam1  =  \n| nationalcaps1  = \n| nationalgoals1 = \n| pcupdate       = 19:43, 8 January 2020 (UTC)\n| ntupdate       = \n}}\n'''Orhan Akta\u015f''' (born 21 October 1994 in [[W\u00fcrselen]]) is a German [[Association football|footballer]] of [[Turkey|Turkish]] descent who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|left back]] for Turkish club [[Manisa FK]]. He is a product of the [[Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach]] Academy.\n\n==Career==\nIn 2010, Akta\u015f joined [[Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach]] at the age of 15. In 2012\u201313 season, he earned 24 appearances for [[Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach]] in the [[Under 19 Bundesliga]] and scored two goals.\n\nOn 19 July 2013, Akta\u015f signed a 3-year contract with [[Denizlispor]] in [[Turkey]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=maraton.com.tr|title=Denizlispor Orhan Akta\u015f'\u0131 transfer etti|url=http://www.maraton.com.tr/denizlispor-orhan-aktasi-transfer-etti_198280.html|date=19 July 2013|language=Turkish}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2015, after a successful trial period, Akta\u015f joined Bulgarian side [[PFC Haskovo|Haskovo]]. He made his league debut in a 1\u20131 away draw against [[PFC Levski Sofia|Levski Sofia]] on 20 March 2015.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=gong.bg|title=Levski 1\u20131 Haskovo|url=http://gong.bg/livescore/bulgaria/a-grupa/levski-fk-haskovo-20-mar-2015-136046|date=20 March 2015|language=Bulgarian}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Soccerway|orhan-akta/260071}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Aktas, Orhan}}\n[[Category:1994 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:German footballers]]\n[[Category:Turkish footballers]]\n[[Category:German people of Turkish descent]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Superettan players]]\n[[Category:First Professional Football League (Bulgaria) players]]\n[[Category:TFF Second League players]]\n[[Category:Husqvarna FF players]]\n[[Category:FC Haskovo players]]\n[[Category:\u0130stanbulspor footballers]]\n[[Category:Giresunspor footballers]]\n[[Category:German expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Sweden]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Bulgaria]]\n\n{{Germany-footy-defender-1990s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Orhan Akta\u015f\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1994|10|21|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[W\u00fcrselen]], [[Germany]]\n| height         = {{height|m=1.75}}\n| position       = [[Defender (association football)|Left back]]<ref>{{WorldFootball.net|orhan-aktas}}</ref>\n| currentclub    = Manisa FK\n| clubnumber     = \n| youthyears1    = \n| youthclubs1    = Blau-Wei\u00df Alsdorf\n| youthyears2    = {{0|0000}}\u20132010\n| youthclubs2    = Germania D\u00fcrwi\u00df\n| youthyears3    = 2010\u20132013\n| youthclubs3    = [[Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach|Borussia M'gladbach]]\n| youthyears4    = 2013\u20132014\n| youthclubs4    = [[Denizlispor]]\n| years1         = 2014\u20132015\n| clubs1         = [[Husqvarna FF]]\n| caps1          = 20\n| goals1         = 0\n| years2         = 2015     \n| clubs2         = [[PFC Haskovo|Haskovo]]\n| caps2          = 10\n| goals2         = 0\n| years3         = 2015\u20132018\n| clubs3         = [[\u0130stanbulspor A.\u015e.|\u0130stanbulspor]]\n| caps3          = 65\n| goals3         = 1\n| years4         = 2018\u20132019\n| clubs4         = BB Bodrumspor\n| caps4          = 42\n| goals4         = 2\n| years5         = 2019\n| clubs5         = [[Giresunspor]]\n| caps5          = 0\n| goals5         = 0\n| years6         = 2020\u2013\n| clubs6         = Manisa FK\n| caps6          = 0\n| goals6         = 0\n| nationalyears1 =           \n| nationalteam1  =  \n| nationalcaps1  = \n| nationalgoals1 = \n| pcupdate       = 19:43, 8 January 2020 (UTC)\n| ntupdate       = \n}}\n'''Orhan Akta\u015f''' (born 21 October 1994 in [[W\u00fcrselen]]) is a German [[Association football|footballer]] of [[Turkey|Turkish]] descent who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|left back]] for Turkish club Manisa FK. He is a product of the [[Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach]] Academy.\n\n==Career==\nIn 2010, Akta\u015f joined [[Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach]] at the age of 15. In 2012\u201313 season, he earned 24 appearances for [[Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach]] in the [[Under 19 Bundesliga]] and scored two goals.\n\nOn 19 July 2013, Akta\u015f signed a 3-year contract with [[Denizlispor]] in [[Turkey]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=maraton.com.tr|title=Denizlispor Orhan Akta\u015f'\u0131 transfer etti|url=http://www.maraton.com.tr/denizlispor-orhan-aktasi-transfer-etti_198280.html|date=19 July 2013|language=Turkish}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2015, after a successful trial period, Akta\u015f joined Bulgarian side [[PFC Haskovo|Haskovo]]. He made his league debut in a 1\u20131 away draw against [[PFC Levski Sofia|Levski Sofia]] on 20 March 2015.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=gong.bg|title=Levski 1\u20131 Haskovo|url=http://gong.bg/livescore/bulgaria/a-grupa/levski-fk-haskovo-20-mar-2015-136046|date=20 March 2015|language=Bulgarian}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Soccerway|orhan-akta/260071}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Aktas, Orhan}}\n[[Category:1994 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:German footballers]]\n[[Category:Turkish footballers]]\n[[Category:German people of Turkish descent]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Superettan players]]\n[[Category:First Professional Football League (Bulgaria) players]]\n[[Category:TFF Second League players]]\n[[Category:Husqvarna FF players]]\n[[Category:FC Haskovo players]]\n[[Category:\u0130stanbulspor footballers]]\n[[Category:Giresunspor footballers]]\n[[Category:German expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Sweden]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Bulgaria]]\n\n{{Germany-footy-defender-1990s-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Geschichte", "label": "safe", "comment": "lk", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orhan_Akta%C5%9F"}
